### Creating a local repository
 use git init command
 
 ### syncing remote with local
 use: git remote add origin "the link to your central repository"
 
 ### Pulling from the central repository
 use: git pull origin master
 
 #### git status 
  tells you which files are added to index and are ready to commit
  
  #### git add
  lets you add files to your index
  
 ### git commit
 snapshots of the repository at a given time
 can't change unless done explicitly
 
 ### checking the status of files on local repo
 use: git status
 
 
 
